President Obama had a phone call with Prime Minister David Cameron of the United Kingdom to discuss Syria and the upcoming London Conference on Supporting Syria and the Region. The President reiterated the commitment of the United States to support those displaced by the violence in Syria and to help alleviate the pressures in Europe caused by the influx of refugees. Secretary of State John Kerry will represent the United States at the conference and announce significant new contributions to support relief efforts. They also discussed plans for a Refugee Summit at the UN General Assembly in September. The leaders talked about the situation in Syria and the need for concrete steps to improve humanitarian access and support the political process. They also discussed efforts to resolve the political impasse in Libya, and Prime Minister Cameron updated President Obama on his negotiations with the European Union to reform the United Kingdom's membership. The President expressed continued support for a strong United Kingdom in a strong European Union.